description:
## Objective
Add Vitest unit tests for `computeWeightedTotal` covering five required cases: typical mid-stage, 0% (Lost) edge, 100% (Won) edge, empty array, single deal. These cases are required by increment 2-wpr's exit criteria — do not drop any.

## Spec Reference
`.devmeta/projects/2026-05-21-stage-probability/2026-05-21-stage-probability-spec.md` — Section: "Test Strategy / Unit tests"

## Scope
**Files:** `src/components/atomic-crm/deals/dealUtils.test.ts` — append a new `describe("computeWeightedTotal", ...)` block alongside the existing tests. Do NOT modify existing tests.

## Implementation
Add at the bottom of the file:
```ts
import { computeWeightedTotal } from "./dealUtils";

describe("computeWeightedTotal", () => {
  it("returns sum(amounts) * probability for a typical mid-stage probability", () => {
    expect(
      computeWeightedTotal(
        [{ amount: 1000 }, { amount: 2000 }, { amount: 5000 }],
        0.5,
      ),
    ).toBe(4000);
  });

  it("returns 0 for any deals when probability is 0 (Lost stage)", () => {
    expect(
      computeWeightedTotal(
        [{ amount: 1000 }, { amount: 2000 }, { amount: 5000 }],
        0,
      ),
    ).toBe(0);
  });

  it("returns sum(amounts) when probability is 1 (Won stage)", () => {
    expect(
      computeWeightedTotal(
        [{ amount: 1000 }, { amount: 2000 }, { amount: 5000 }],
        1,
      ),
    ).toBe(8000);
  });

  it("returns 0 for an empty deals array regardless of probability", () => {
    expect(computeWeightedTotal([], 0.5)).toBe(0);
    expect(computeWeightedTotal([], 1)).toBe(0);
  });

  it("returns amount * probability for a single deal", () => {
    expect(computeWeightedTotal([{ amount: 1234 }], 0.25)).toBe(308.5);
  });
});
```

(If `computeWeightedTotal` is already exported from dealUtils.ts there is no need to add the import twice — adjust if formatISODateString-style imports collide.)

## Tests
Run: `npx vitest run src/components/atomic-crm/deals/dealUtils.test.ts`
Do NOT close until tests pass.
